'''Sherel Floranus''' (born 23 August 1998) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[right-back]] for {{Dutch football updater|PECZwolle}} club [[PEC Zwolle]].<ref name="soccerway">{{Soccerway|sherel-floranus/385271}}</ref> Born in the Netherlands, he plays for the [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao national team]].

==Club career==
Floranus is a youth exponent from [[Sparta Rotterdam]]. He made his team debut on 21 August 2015 against [[FC Eindhoven]] starting in the first eleven and was replaced after 81 minutes by Denzel Dumfries.<ref name="soccerway2">{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2015/10/04/netherlands/eredivisie/bv-de-graafschap/feyenoord-rotterdam-nv/2039318/|title=Sparta Rotterdam vs. FC Eindhoven – 21 August 2015 – Soccerway|publisher=soccerway.com|access-date=10 October 2015}}</ref>

On 1 August 2023, Floranus signed a two-year contract with [[Almere City FC|Almere City]], freshly promoted to [[Eredivisie]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Almere City|url=https://almerecity.nl/almere-city-1/sherel-floranus-versterkt-verdediging-almere-city-fc/|title=Sherel Floranus versterkt verdediging Almere City FC|trans-title=Sherel Floranus strengthens Almere City FC's defense|date=1 August 2023|access-date=1 August 2023|language=nl}}</ref>

On 26 August 2024, Floranus moved to [[PEC Zwolle]] on a three-season deal.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=PEC Zwolle|url=https://peczwolle.nl/nieuws/pec-zwolle-haalt-ervaren-sherel-floranus-binnen|title=PEC Zwolle haalt ervaren Sherel Floranus binnen|trans-title=PEC Zwolle brings in experienced Sherel Floranus|date=26 August 2024|access-date=26 August 2024|language=nl}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in the Netherlands, Floranus is of Curaçaoan descent. He is a youth international for the Netherlands. In June 2021 He was called up to [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao]]'s preliminary squad for the [[2021 CONCACAF Gold Cup]].<ref name=":0">{{cite web|date=18 June 2021|title=2021 Concacaf Gold Cup preliminary rosters announced|url=https://www.concacaf.com/gold-cup/article/2021-concacaf-gold-cup-preliminary-rosters-announced/|access-date=19 June 2021|publisher=CONCACAF}}</ref>

